    <item>
      <title>Research To Policy Convening: Drivers &amp; Solutions to Wealth Inequality at Howard University – Interdisciplinary Research Building 2021 Georgia Ave, NW Washington, DC 20059</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52445544688547/huge/f4d369d63f457dfcdbcf21254c1bf8e4fb984373.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Mon, 04 May 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>Howard University’s WEALTH Institute will host Research to Policy: Drivers &amp; Solutions to Wealth Inequality -- the inaugural convening that will bring together leading researchers, policy experts, advocates, and community leaders to explore evidence-based strategies to address the persistent drivers of the Black wealth gap.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Through a series of discussions and collaborative exchanges, participants will examine how interconnected systems—including housing stability, inheritance and estate planning, health outcomes, and access to legal and financial resources—shape economic mobility and long-term wealth building. The convening will highlight critical research, elevate lived experiences, and identify practical policy pathways that can advance equity and opportunity.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Designed for researchers, policymakers, nonprofit leaders, students, and community partners, this convening will create space for interdisciplinary dialogue and collaboration focused on translating research into actionable policy solutions.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Registration is required. Additional details—including the full agenda, speakers, and logistical information—will be shared with registered participants in the coming weeks.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Contact Email: <a href="mailto:e2s2@howard.edu">e2s2@howard.edu</a> and <a href="mailto:HowardWealth@raben.co">HowardWealth@raben.co</a></p>

<p><a href="https://events.howard.edu/event/research-to-policy-convening-drivers-solutions-to-wealth-inequality">View on site</a> | <a href="mailto:?subject=I found an interesting event%3A Research To Policy Convening%3A Drivers %26 Solutions to Wealth Inequality&amp;body=I found an interesting event you may like%3A%0A%0A%0ADate%3A May 4%2C 2026%0A%0ADescription%3A%0AHoward University%E2%80%99s WEALTH Institute will host Research to Policy%3A Drivers %26 Solutions to Wealth Inequality -- the inaugural convening that will bring together leading researchers%2C policy experts%2C advocates%2C and community leaders to explore evidence-based strategies to address the persistent drivers of the Black wealth gap.%0A%0A %0A%0AThrough a series of discussions and collaborative exchanges%2C participants will examine how interconnected systems%E2%80%94including housing stability%2C inheritance and estate planning%2C health outcomes%2C and access to legal and financial resources%E2%80%94shape economic mobility and long-term wealth building. The convening will highlight critical research%2C elevate lived experiences%2C and identify practical policy pathways that can advance equity and opportunity.%0A%0A %0A%0ADesigned for researchers%2C policymakers%2C nonprofit leaders%2C students%2C and community partners%2C this convening will create space for interdisciplinary dialogue and collaboration focused on translating research into actionable policy solutions.%0A%0A %0A%0ARegistration is required. Additional details%E2%80%94including the full agenda%2C speakers%2C and logistical information%E2%80%94will be shared with registered participants in the coming weeks.%0A%0A %0A%0AContact Email%3A e2s2%40howard.edu and HowardWealth%40raben.co%0A%0Ahttps%3A%2F%2Fevents.howard.edu%2Fevent%2Fresearch-to-policy-convening-drivers-solutions-to-wealth-inequality%0A">Email this event</a></p></div></div>]]></description>
