      <title>Faculty Info Session: AI Certificate + Submit a Course for 'AI in the Disciplines' Designation</title>
      <description><![CDATA[<div>  <img src="https://localist-images.azureedge.net/photos/52755604703874/huge/0ba95ce8cde875aa4be97b17dd4b76f45c32ff7a.jpg" style="width: 100%;" />  <div style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"><strong>Tue, 05 May 2026</strong></div>  <div><p>The Fundamentals of AI Certificate has been officially approved! We invite faculty to learn how to submit a course for designation as an AI in the Disciplines course.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>As part of the certificate, students complete:</p>

<p>EGPP 421 – Intro to AI Tools and TechniquesEGPP 422 – Ethical and Responsible AIOne approved AI in the Disciplines course </p>

<p>During the virtual information session, we will review student learning outcomes, walk through the review process, and answer questions. If you are unable to attend, the session will be recorded—please register so we can share it with you. This session is open to the Howard University community.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Session Details: Tuesday, May 5 | 12:00–1:00 PM EST</p>

<p>Zoom Registration: <a href="https://howard.zoom.us/meeting/register/7QcT6IBDR0C5Y-3I7fjoeA">https://howard.zoom.us/meeting/register/7QcT6IBDR0C5Y-3I7fjoeA</a></p>

<p> </p>

<p>All disciplines are welcome. For questions, contact <a href="mailto:AI@howard.edu">AI@howard.edu</a>.</p>

<p> </p>

<p>Plesee note that students can register for Fall 2026 AI courses here: <a href="https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/cGxswavbBh">https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/cGxswavbBh</a></p>

